## Repository Structure (high level)
alice-v2/
- services/
  - orchestrator/        # LLM routing, planner, observability
  - guardian/            # Safety gate and state machine
  - eval/                # Autonomous E2E harness
  - loadgen/             # Brownout/load tests
- monitoring/            # HUD and dashboards
- scripts/               # Auto-verify, helpers
- data/                  # telemetry/ and tests/
- test-results/          # nightly trends
- .cursor/rules/         # Architecture-first rules (PRD/ADR/workflow/structure)

## Conventions
- Python services: FastAPI + Pydantic, structlog, env-driven config
- Telemetry: JSONL under data/telemetry/YYYY-MM-DD/
- Tests: artifacts under data/tests/
- Security: Guardian enforced; security policy via config/security_policy.yaml

## Editing Guidance for AI (Cursor)
- Respect this structure; do not introduce new top-level dirs without ADR
- Keep edits small and observable; update ADR/PRD when decisions change
